<p>the opposite direction knocked 3 chaps off our tram one fellow fell underneath &amp; was killed another poor chap was seriously injured &amp; the 3rd one escaped with a few cuts &amp; bruises,  we rarely used to pay our fares on these trams when going home, they used to tell the conductor to "put it down to Kitchener"<br/>The Heliopolis tram service is a clinker more like a train than any thing else she travels very fast &amp; is well fitted up, easily the best I have seen so far.<br/>The Kursall" was the principal theatre in Cairo for the soldiers they used to put on a fair show at times there a sort of music hall</p>
